mailto-gmail - A script to use Gmail as default email client.
Copyright 2010 Jesús Torres <aplatanado@gulic.org>


Description
-----------

mailto-gmail is a Perl script that opens the compose mail page of Gmail in the
default browser, filling fields like To or Cc with the information provides by
the user trough the command-line arguments.

This script allows to use Gmail as default email client, much like any other
desktop client.


Usage
-----

mailto-gmail only needs the recipient address, for instance:

$ ./mailto-gmail user@mail.com

It also have options like '--subject', '--cc', '--bcc' and '--body' to specify
the email fields. Futher, mailto-gmail supports the Gmail in Google Apps
trough the option '--domain'. If it appears in command-line, the script will
open the Gmail in Google Apps for the specified domain instead of the generic
one.


